----------Getting Started with TypeScript-----------------
TypeScript needs to be transpiled into JavaScript
To be able to debug TypeScript in the browser, we need to create a source map
    --The source map maps the transpiled javascript into the TypeScript source

--Install TypeScript Globally via npm
->npm install typescript -g

--To create the source map, we use the tsc command installed from TypeScript
->tsc --sourceMap true [yourTypeScriptFile.ts]

--To compile typescript code into javascript, we typescript
->tsc [yourTypeScriptFile.ts]

--Install TSLint for VSCode 
--Install TSLint Globally via npm
->npm install tslint -g

TSLint keeps coding for typescript clean 
-It uses a tslint.json file to hold all the linting rules

---Configure Grunt for TypeScript ---------
--Install Grunt via
->npm install grunt grunt-ts grunt-tslint tslint typescript --save-dev

Run by typing in grunt in the terminal to compile
->grunt

----Jasmine--------------------------------
Behavior driven testing framework
Install Jasmine via npm
->npm install jasmine -g

jasmine configuration settings are stored in a jasmin.json file stored in a spec/support directory
to create a jasmine file, enter: jasmine init
->jasmine init 

Create a Suite and Specs
Suite -- A suite defines what is being tested i.e. unit tests
Specs -- contains expectations and assertions that are true or false

To run unit tests in jasmine type in 
->jasmine
